# Import Path Convention

Always use the `@/` path alias for imports from the project's `src` directory. Do not use relative paths (`./` or `../`).

## Rule

- Use `@/` for all project imports (components, hooks, types, utils, etc.)
- The `@/` alias resolves to `src/`

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - relative imports
import { getEncounters } from "./data";
import { EncountersTable } from "../encountersTable";
import { translations } from "../../i18n/translations";

// ✅ GOOD - @/ alias
import { getEncounters } from "@/app/api/encounters/data";
import { EncountersTable } from "@/components/Encounters/encountersTable";
import { translations } from "@/i18n/translations";
```

## Apply consistently

When adding new imports or refactoring, use `@/` throughout the project.
